  <title>Manual selection</title>

  <para>This modifier allows to select particles manually in the viewports.
  The modifier stores the selection state of all particles in an internal array. The parameter panel of the 
  modifier provides several functions to modify the stored selection set. 
  When the modifier acts on the input particles, it replaces any existing particle selection state
  with its stored selection state.</para>

  <para>When the <guibutton>Pick particles</guibutton> mode is activated, individual particles
  can be selected or deselected by clicking on them in the viewports.</para>

  <para>When the <guibutton>Fence selection</guibutton> mode is activated, 
  the mouse can be used to draw a closed fence around a group of particles in the viewports.
  All particles within the fence polygon will be selected.</para>
  
</section>
